frontNews.title: Cruise ships quarantined over coronavirus
frontNews.desc: American passengers on the coronavirus-stricken Diamond Princess cruise ship departed from a Tokyo airport early Monday on flights home that the U.S. government arranged after a high-level political push in Washington.

frontNews.title: Kirk Douglas, Hollywood legend and star of Spartacus, dies aged 103
frontNews.desc: Kirk Douglas, the self-styled “ragman’s son” who became the last great star of Hollywood’s golden age, has died at the age of 103.

frontNews.title: Newborn among 28,000 coronavirus cases as death toll passes 550
frontNews.desc: The death toll from coronavirus has passed 550, it was confirmed on Wednesday, as Chinese media reported that a baby had been diagnosed with the virus just 30 hours after birth, the youngest case recorded so far.

frontNews.title: US threatens Venezuela with 'crippling' measures after Trump-Guaidó meeting
frontNews.desc: The United States has warned it was preparing “crippling” and “impactful measures” designed to force Nicolás Maduro from power as Donald Trump rolled out the red carpet for the Venezuelan leader’s challenger, Juan Guaidó.
